{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":537,"text":"In 1991 I had"},{"time":2363,"text":"maybe the most profound and transformative"},{"time":5121,"text":"experience of my life."},{"time":6687,"text":"I was in the third year of my seven-year undergraduate degree."},{"time":11414,"text":"I took a couple victory laps in there."},{"time":13605,"text":"And I was on a college choir tour up in Northern California,"},{"time":17827,"text":"and we had stopped for the day after all day on the bus,"},{"time":20484,"text":"and we were relaxing next to this beautiful"},{"time":22550,"text":"idyllic lake in the mountains."},{"time":24739,"text":"And there were crickets and birds and frogs making noise,"},{"time":29135,"text":"and as we sat there, over the mountains coming in"},{"time":31851,"text":"from the north were these Steven Spielbergian clouds"},{"time":34819,"text":"rolling toward us,"},{"time":36292,"text":"and as the clouds got about halfway over the valley,"},{"time":38939,"text":"so help me God, every single animal in that place"},{"time":43337,"text":"stopped making noise at the same time."},{"time":45553,"text":"(Whoosh) This electric hush, as if they could sense what was about to happen."},{"time":50637,"text":"And then the clouds came over us, and then,"},{"time":52697,"text":"boom! This massive thunderclap, and sheets of rain."},{"time":57007,"text":"It was just extraordinary, and when I came back home"},{"time":60469,"text":"I found a poem by the Mexican poet Octavio Paz,"},{"time":63472,"text":"and decided to set it to music,"},{"time":65973,"text":"a piece for choir called \"Cloudburst,\""},{"time":68154,"text":"which is the piece that we'll perform for you in just a moment."}]},{"cues":[{"time":71317,"text":"Now fast forward to just three years ago."},{"time":75692,"text":"(Music) And we released to YouTube this,"},{"time":79133,"text":"the Virtual Choir Project,"},{"time":81389,"text":"185 singers from 12 different countries."},{"time":84596,"text":"You can see my little video there conducting these people,"},{"time":88033,"text":"alone in their dorm rooms"},{"time":89188,"text":"or in their living rooms at home."},{"time":92277,"text":"Two years ago, on this very stage, we premiered"},{"time":96003,"text":"Virtual Choir 2,"},{"time":99550,"text":"2,052 singers from 58 different countries,"},{"time":104112,"text":"this time performing a piece that I had written called \"Sleep.\""},{"time":107403,"text":"And then just last spring we released Virtual Choir 3,"},{"time":112697,"text":"\"Water Night,\" another piece that I had written,"},{"time":115253,"text":"this time nearly 4,000 singers from 73 different countries."},{"time":121517,"text":"(Music)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":126936,"text":"And when I was speaking to Chris about the future"},{"time":129943,"text":"of Virtual Choir and where we might be able to take this,"},{"time":132093,"text":"he challenged me to push the technology as far as we possibly could."},{"time":136854,"text":"Could we do this all in real time?"},{"time":139357,"text":"Could we have people singing together in real time?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":142397,"text":"And with the help of Skype,"},{"time":143992,"text":"that is what we are going to attempt today."},{"time":146096,"text":"Now, we'll perform \"Cloudburst\" for you."},{"time":148269,"text":"The first half will be performed by the live singers here on stage."},{"time":151421,"text":"I'm joined by singers from Cal State Long Beach,"},{"time":153917,"text":"Cal State Fullerton and Riverside Community College,"},{"time":157245,"text":"some of the best amateur choirs in the country, and â€”"},{"time":160565,"text":"(Applause) --"},{"time":167603,"text":"and in the second half of the piece,"},{"time":169789,"text":"the virtual choir will join us, 30 different singers"},{"time":172611,"text":"from 30 different countries."}]},{"cues":[{"time":174661,"text":"Now, we've pushed the technology as far as it can go,"},{"time":177245,"text":"but there's still less than a second of latency,"},{"time":180077,"text":"but in musical terms, that's a lifetime."},{"time":182156,"text":"We deal in milliseconds."},{"time":183608,"text":"So what I've done is, I've adapted \"Cloudburst\""},{"time":186075,"text":"so that it embraces the latency"},{"time":188578,"text":"and the performers sing into the latency"},{"time":191483,"text":"instead of trying to be exactly together."}]},{"cues":[{"time":193981,"text":"So with deep humility, and for your approval,"},{"time":197245,"text":"we present \"Cloudburst.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":199357,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":204076,"text":"(Piano)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":210249,"text":"[The rain ...]"},{"time":221142,"text":"[Eyes of shadow-water]"},{"time":226253,"text":"[eyes of well-water]"},{"time":244512,"text":"[eyes of dream-water.]"},{"time":255439,"text":"[Blue suns, green whirlwinds,]"},{"time":273919,"text":"[birdbeaks of light pecking open]"},{"time":281687,"text":"[pomegranate stars.]"},{"time":291694,"text":"[But tell me, burnt earth, is there no water?]"},{"time":310311,"text":"[Only blood, only dust,]"},{"time":318239,"text":"[only naked footsteps on the thorns?]"},{"time":334903,"text":"[The rain awakens...]"},{"time":352271,"text":"[We must sleep with open eyes,]"},{"time":355583,"text":"[we must dream with our hands,]"},{"time":368140,"text":"[we must dream the dreams of a river seeking its course,]"},{"time":373191,"text":"[of the sun dreaming its worlds.]"},{"time":387628,"text":"[We must dream aloud,]"},{"time":408967,"text":"[we must sing till the song puts forth roots,]"},{"time":435759,"text":"[trunk, branches, birds, stars.]"},{"time":465475,"text":"[We must find the lost word,]"},{"time":480322,"text":"[and remember what the blood,]"},{"time":488187,"text":"[the tides, the earth, and the body say,]"},{"time":514991,"text":"[and return to the point of departure...]"}]},{"cues":[{"time":532561,"text":"(Music)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":682745,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":697169,"text":"[\"Cloudburst\" Octavio Paz][translation by Lysander Kemp, adapted by Eric Whitacre]"}]},{"cues":[{"time":699478,"text":"Eric Whitacre: Beth. Annabelle, where are you? Jacob."},{"time":706881,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":728622,"text":"Thank you."}]}]}